  "body": "## Preamble\r\nVIP: [#648](https://github.com/ethereum/vyper/issues/648)\r\nTitle: Solidity to Vyper translator\r\nAuthor: @Johan-Pretorius\r\nType: Standard Track\r\nStatus: Draft\r\nCreated: 2018-01-26\r\n\r\n## Simple Summary\r\nIf one can convert Solidity contracts to Vyper code, one can leverage a huge amount of previous work and build on to it.\r\n\r\n## Abstract\r\nOne of the most powerful aspects of open-development communities is the ability to leverage work that was done by others (etc openZeppelin, ERC-20, MiniMe all get used and extended to build new tools). It would be extremely useful if there was a converter from Solidity to Vyper, so that work done in Solidity can be ported to, and extended in, Vyper.\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nThe motivation is to enable developers to jump-start being productive by leveraging the mass of work that has already been done in Solidity.\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\n1. Download source Solidity contract (and all contracts in the hierarchy tree).\r\n2. Run a tool to translate source Solidity contracts into Vyper code.\r\n3. Output new Vyper source code file.\r\n\r\n## Backwards Compatibility\r\nA new tool, hence no backward compatibility issues.\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via CC0\r\n",
