    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Neither language is that complicated, but both make very different tradeoffs that would make creating a tool like this very difficult. Namely, solidity leverages inheritance to a large extent, whereas Vyper disallows it and currently doesn't have a method for program extension (although we're looking into composition as a model). Each language has to deal with many different small security tradeoffs, so this is not something that can be trivially rewritten by a translator.\r\n\r\nOnce Vyper gets more traction, people will create libraries of model code like OpenZeppelin has done with solidity. Smart contracts are not hugely complicated codebases, and can be translated manually in a few days to a few weeks without an automated tool. Wouldn't you much rather have a security expert well versed in this nuance accomplish this task, over some tool that could never understand that nuance when you have thousands to millions of dollars on the line?\r\n\r\nThat being said, having a section in the docs about translated as thing Solidity to Vyper would be handy.",
